name: PerformanceEntry
description: The PerformanceEntry object encapsulates a single performance metric that is part of the performance timeline. A performance entry can be directly created by making a performance mark or measure (for example by calling the mark() method) at an explicit point in an application. Performance entries are also created in indirect ways such as loading a resource (such as an image).

members.name: PerformanceEntry.name
members.description: A DOMString representing the name of a performance entry when the metric was created.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.entryType
members.description: A DOMString representing the type of performance metric such as "mark". See entryType for a list of valid values.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.startTime
members.description: A DOMHighResTimeStamp representing the starting time for the performance metric.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.duration
members.description: A DOMHighResTimeStamp representing the time value of the duration of the performance event.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.toJSON()
members.description: A jsonizer that returns a JSON representation of the PerformanceEntry object.

parameters.name: json
parameters.description: A JSON object that is the serialization of the PerformanceEntry object.
